                    "line": 23,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Matt Spinler",
                        "email": "spinler@us.ibm.com",
                        "username": "spinler"
                    },
                    "message": "I think it would be useful to have this information in the event log so you know what went wrong in the field.  There's two ways I can think of:\n\n1. Pass it into createError() inside the additionalData variable, like \"ERROR\": TPM measurement file...\"\"\n2.  Have the PEL message registry entry capture the journal.\n\nThe first method allows people that don't use PELs to also get the info in the D-Bus event log."
                },
                {
                    "file": "secure_boot_check.cpp",
                    "line": 23,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Geissler",
                        "email": "geissonator@yahoo.com",
                        "username": "geissonator"
                    },
                    "message": "Yeah, we'll def want to know why we failed in the log. Also, are we sure every system that will run this function will have this TPM path? If it's easier you can just create the error in this function."
                },
                {
                    "file": "secure_boot_check.cpp",
                    "line": 23,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Lakshmi Yadlapati",
                        "email": "lakshmiy@us.ibm.com",
                        "username": "Lakshmi-y"
                    },
                    "message": "I updated the function to add additional data.\nYes, every system will have this PATH, Eddie dropped this change in Linux Repo."
                },
